Ensure that HTTP headers are used to prevent caching. Your application can use certain HTTP headers to prevent certain content from being cached. Ensure that the following techniques are used:
      
        Verify that sensitive content contains the header "Pragma: No-Cache" in the outputted HTML document. Example: <HTML>    <HEAD>        <HTTP-EQUIV="PRAGMA" CONTENT="NO-CACHE">        ...    </HEAD>    <BODY>        ...    </BODY></HTML>
        Verify that your application includes the "Cache-Control: no-cache" header in the outputted HTTP response. Example: Response.Cache.SetCacheability(HttpCacheability.NoCache);
